ns-serif; text-align: justify; user-select: initial !important;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; user-select: initial !important; font-size: medium;\">I believed… there is no such thing as a “sexual problem” because, then, allopathic doctors declared that… sexual difficulties occur only due to mental (psychogenic) confusions or disorders and there are no known physical causes responsible for erectile dysfunction.</span></p><p style=\"margin: 8px; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; font-size: 14px; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify; user-select: initial !important;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; user-select: initial !important; font-size: medium;\">Therefore my general belief was… the doctor who claims that he has a cure for the sexual problem is a useless form of \'medication\' dispensed by a quack.</span></p><p style=\"margin: 8px; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; font-size: 14px; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify; user-select: initial !important;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; user-select: initial !important; font-size: medium;\">I got married at the age of 30 and enjoyed my sexual life without any problem for the first 2 years, then one day I noticed that my erection strength has decreased drastically but I neglected it considering it as a result of psychological tension.</span></p><p style=\"margin: 8px; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; font-size: 14px; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify; user-select: initial !important;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; user-select: initial !important; font-size: medium;\">But it got worse day by day and I was not able to maintain an erection as long as I used to be before and I can\'t even get an erection looking at porn or reading sexually explicit stories.</span></p><p style=\"margin: 8px; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; font-size: 14px; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify; user-select: initial !important;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; user-select: initial !important; font-size: medium;\">So I approached a psychiatrist for consultation and underwent psychiatric treatment for 6 months which was ineffective!</span></p><p style=\"margin: 8px; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; font-size: 14px; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify; user-select: initial !important;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; user-select: initial !important; font-size: medium;\">But tirelessly I approached many specialist doctors (UROLOGIST- ANDROLOGIST), but to my disappointment, they gave me the same explanation such as:-</span></p><p style=\"margin: 8px; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; font-size: 14px; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify; user-select: initial !important;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; user-select: initial !important; font-size: medium;\">Psychological problems: The most common nonphysical causes are stress, anxiety, and fatigue. Impotence is a side effect of psychological problems such as depression.</span></p><p style=\"margin: 8px; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; font-size: 14px; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify; user-select: initial !important;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; user-select: initial !important; font-size: medium;\">Negative feelings: Feelings that you express toward your sexual partner — or that are expressed by your sexual partners — such as resentment, hostility, or lack of interest also can be a factor in erectile dysfunction.</span></p><p style=\"margin: 8px; padding: 0px; line-height: 26px; font-size: 14px; color: rgb(68, 68, 68); font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; text-align: justify; user-select: initial !important;\"><span 